r noreferrer">$5,220</a></strong></td><td><strong>9/10 — The Carat Hunter.</strong> At 2.36 carats, this is significantly larger than the 2.0ct IGI options below but priced hundreds of dollars cheaper. This is the benefit of shopping GCAL over IGI for high-spec labs in 2026.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td>IGI</td><td>2.00ct</td><td>D-IF</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28885386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$5,580</a></strong></td><td><strong>7/10 — The IGI Premium.</strong> A standard 2.00-carat milestone stone. While it carries a premium over the GCAL options, IGI is the global industry standard for lab diamonds, providing excellent resale liquidity (relatively speaking).</td></tr><tr><td>IGI</td><td>2.00ct</td><td>D-IF</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27426168?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$5,580</a></strong></td><td><strong>7/10 — Reliable Quality.</strong> Identical in spec and price to the previous stone. This represents the stable market median for high-tier lab stones in May 2026.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td>IGI</td><td>2.01ct</td><td>D-IF</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28449573?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$5,610</a></strong></td><td><strong>8/10 — The Precision Pick.</strong> A minor price step-up for the 2.01ct mark. This stone likely features slightly better symmetry scores, ensuring the 57-facet pattern is perfectly aligned for maximum light return.</td></tr><tr><td>IGI</td><td>2.01ct</td><td>D-IF</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27420176?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target